import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='budgetYear')
    plt.plot(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget allocation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['value'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['value'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecast values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['budgetYear'], data['value'], color='blue', label='Budget')
    plt.scatter(data['forecastYear'], data['value'], color='red', label='Forecast')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between budget and forecast values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce').dt.year
    data = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['value'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Average budget allocation'])
    plt.title('What is the average budget allocation per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
